    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce" percent="70.0">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Data gathered in two clay bricks factories through a process assessment in a technical visit. The production process of this material is artisanal and most of factories in Ecuador have a similar process and raw materials. According to a study conducted by Swisscontact in Cuenca in 2016, 89% of brick factories are considered artisanal (which produce clay brick moulded) and the rest semi-mechanized. Land occupation exchange is used as an estimate of infrastructure.

References: Venegas, O. (2018). Evaluación de la energía contenida, emisiones de CO2 y material particulado en la fabricación del ladrillo semi-mecanizado tochano en cuenca, a través del análisis de ciclo de vida (ACV). [Master degree in Constructions, University of Cuenca]. https://dspace.ucuenca.edu.ec/bitstream/123456789/29319/1/MscArqAndr%C3%A9sVenegas.pdf

</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Data are calculated as a weighted average between the data collected at the two clay brick artisanal production factories. See exchange comments for further details.

</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
